<p><a href="http://mpmath.org/" rel="nofollow"><code>mpmath</code></a> purports to support "arbitrary-precision floating-point arithmetic."</p>  <p>And yet . . .</p>  <pre><code>&gt;&gt;&gt; import mpmath &gt;&gt;&gt; 1 + mpmath.erf(-5.921) mpf('1.1102230246251565e-16') &gt;&gt;&gt; 1 + mpmath.erf(-5.922)  # I expect a smaller positive number here. mpf('0.0') </code></pre>  <p>Am I missing something?  Or is this a fundamental limitation of <code>mpmath</code>?</p>  <p>@jonrsharpe has suggested that the problem is that I've submitted a <code>float</code> to <code>erf</code>.  However, the code below shows that this is not the problem:</p>  <pre><code>&gt;&gt;&gt; 1 + mpmath.erf(mpmath.mpf('-5.922')) mpf('0.0') </code></pre>